label: An Architectural Guide to Charleston, South Carolina, Colonial Period, No. 12: Bermuda Stone House
description: Description and details of the Bermuda Stone House, 141 and 143-145 Church Street, No. 12, written by Albert Simons. Keywords and phrases include St. Phillips Street, coral stone, ballast, Charles Town, "Pirate Houses", duplex, narrow passage, coral stone masonry, stucco, cornice, eaves, single brick chimney, arched hoods, Greek Revival, and graft pseudo colonial doorways.
